  ('latest_sermons', 'list.filter_expository.label', 'Expository', 'text'),
  ('latest_sermons', 'list.filter_narrative.label', 'Narrative', 'text'),
  ('latest_sermons', 'list.filter_textual.label', 'Textual', 'text'),
  ('latest_sermons', 'list.filter_topical.label', 'Topical', 'text'),
  ('latest_sermons', 'list.search.placeholder', 'Search sermons, scripture, or series…', 'text'),
  ('latest_sermons', 'list.title', 'All sermons', 'text'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'body.p1', 'The Children’s Ministry helps children grow and develop into spiritual teens, young adults, and ultimately spiritual men/women of God, who will make a lasting impact for the Kingdom of Christ. Through the various children’s ministries here at Shiloh, we believe that a firm spiritual foundation can be made that will anchor our children forever. Children’s Church meets 2nd, 3rd, & 4th Sunday. Nursery meets every Sunday.We have a vibrant curriculum that children love and learn from, as well as family resources designed to meet the needs of today’s families. Children are encouraged to open their hearts to God through worship and study in a safe and loving environment.Our Nursery- Kinder Director, Monique Rios, and our Children’s Director, Juli Godsil, are both available to help you in the most important task any parent can have – helping your child develop a relationship with God!Heaven makes space for every child and so do we.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'body.p2', 'For some kids, we have the joy of working a little harder to make sure they are welcomed well. We call this our Breakthrough ministry and we seek to support neuro-diverse and special needs children. Parents and staff collaborate to find the best fit for the child. We have three different approaches:Early Years (Ages 0-6): Inclusion modelElementary (1st – 6th Grade): Inclusion modelBreakthrough (1st Grade – 18 years old): Sensory sensitive classroom', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'body.p3', 'We believe our church is richer for these little ones and we seek to partner with Gods’ dreams and purposes for them. For more information and to notify us that your child will be joining us, please email: example@cmsmasters.com', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'hero.title', 'Ask Bishop', 'text'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'meta.title', 'Ask Bishop', 'text'),
  ('ministry.ask_bishop', 'sections.h3_1', 'Welcome to Small Groups Ministry!', 'text'),
  ('ministry.family', 'body.p1', 'Family is at the center of God’s design, and YDM’s Family Ministry is devoted to helping families thrive in faith and unity. Bishop H. O. Wilson, as a Licensed Marriage Officer, brings biblical wisdom and compassion to weddings, pre-marital counseling, and marriage ceremonies. These services honor the sacred covenant of marriage and prepare couples for lifelong commitment built on a Christ-centered foundation.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.family', 'body.p2', 'In addition to marriage, the ministry provides baby and child dedication services, affirming parents’ desire to raise their children in the faith and committing the church community to support them. Through consistent teaching and practical biblical guidance, YDM empowers families to build homes where love, prayer, and faith are central.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.family', 'body.p3', 'The Family Ministry extends its impact through parenting workshops and family seminars that address the unique challenges of today’s households. Bishop Wilson also facilitates marriage enrichment retreats where couples can strengthen their bond and rediscover joy in their relationship. Whether counseling young couples, supporting parents in their spiritual responsibilities, or guiding families through difficult seasons, YDM provides care and teaching that nurture healthy, Christ-centered families.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.family', 'body.p4', 'This ministry believes that when families are strong, the church and community become stronger as well. By providing biblical tools, supportive community, and practical guidance, the Family Ministry helps families build a legacy of faith that can be passed on for generations.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.family', 'hero.title', 'Family Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.family', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.family', 'meta.title', 'Family Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.family', 'sections.h3_1', 'Welcome to Children’s Ministry!', 'text'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'body.p1', 'Strong churches are built on strong leaders, and the Leadership & Development Ministry at YDM exists to equip men and women for excellence in service. Under the guidance of Bishop H. O. Wilson, this ministry focuses on developing leaders who are biblically grounded, Spirit-led, and practically prepared to face the challenges of ministry today.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'body.p2', 'Leadership training programs cover everything from preaching and teaching skills to organizational development, pastoral care, and effective communication. These training opportunities are designed not only for current leaders but also for those who feel the call of God on their lives and want to be mentored into greater roles of responsibility. Through teaching, encouragement, and hands-on experience, YDM helps leaders rise to their full potential in Christ.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'body.p3', 'Beyond structured training, the Leadership & Development Ministry provides mentorship for pastors, ministers, and emerging leaders who desire personal guidance and spiritual accountability. Bishop Wilson also facilitates leadership retreats and conferences that allow participants to step away from daily responsibilities and focus on renewal, vision, and growth.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'body.p4', 'Recognizing the importance of accessibility, online training modules are also being developed to ensure that leaders worldwide can benefit from YDM’s leadership resources. The heartbeat of this ministry is to invest in leaders who will, in turn, disciple others and multiply the work of the Kingdom. By equipping leaders with both spiritual depth and practical skill, YDM ensures that the church remains strong, relevant, and effective in its mission.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'hero.title', 'Leadership & Development', 'text'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'meta.title', 'Leadership & Development', 'text'),
  ('ministry.leadership', 'sections.h3_1', 'Leadership & Development Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'body.p1', 'The Compassion & Outreach Ministry at YDM exists to embody the love of Christ by reaching beyond the walls of the church to those most in need. Bishop H. O. Wilson leads this ministry with a heart of service, bringing comfort, encouragement, and hope to the sick, the elderly, the incarcerated, and the marginalized.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'body.p2', 'Hospital ministry provides prayer and support to those walking through illness, while senior nursing home visits offer fellowship and compassion to elders who may feel forgotten. Prison ministry brings the light of Christ to those behind bars, offering spiritual counsel, encouragement, and a reminder of God’s unchanging love. Chaplaincy services extend YDM’s reach into diverse settings, offering pastoral care to people of all backgrounds and circumstances.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'body.p3', 'In addition to these vital ministries, the Compassion & Outreach Ministry organizes community food and clothing drives that meet practical needs while opening doors for gospel conversations. Youth mentorship and outreach programs also provide guidance and encouragement to young people, helping them make wise choices and find purpose in Christ.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'body.p4', 'At its heart, this ministry reflects the compassion of Jesus, who cared for the poor, the sick, and the oppressed. Every outreach effort is grounded in the belief that small acts of kindness can lead to eternal transformation. By partnering with YDM in outreach, you are helping to touch lives with the healing, hope, and love of Christ.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'hero.title', 'Compassion & Outreach', 'text'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'meta.title', 'Compassion & Outreach', 'text'),
  ('ministry.outreach', 'sections.h3_1', 'Compassion & Outreach Ministry!', 'text'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'body.p1', 'The Partnership & Support Ministry invites individuals and families to join hands with YDM in advancing the Kingdom of God. Ministry is never meant to be done alone, and Bishop H. O. Wilson believes in the power of shared vision and partnership.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'body.p2', 'By standing with YDM through prayer, giving, and encouragement, partners become part of every soul touched, every leader trained, and every community reached. Opportunities to partner financially ensure that YDM’s ministries remain strong, sustainable, and able to expand into new areas of impact.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'body.p3', 'A commitment to excellence in stewardship and service means every contribution is used effectively for Kingdom work.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'body.p4', 'For some kids, we have the joy of working a little harder to make sure they are welcomed well. We call this our Breakthrough ministry and we seek to support neuro-diverse and special needs children. Parents and staff collaborate to find the best fit for the child. We have three different approaches:Early Years (Ages 0-6): Inclusion modelElementary (1st – 6th Grade): Inclusion modelBreakthrough (1st Grade – 18 years old): Sensory sensitive classroom', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'body.p5', 'We believe our church is richer for these little ones and we seek to partner with Gods’ dreams and purposes for them. For more information and to notify us that your child will be joining us, please email: example@cmsmasters.com', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'hero.title', 'Partnership & Support Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.partnership', 'meta.title', 'Partnership & Support Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'body.p1', 'The Worldwide Ministry (Online) is YDM’s commitment to spreading the gospel beyond geographical limits. Through modern technology and digital platforms, Bishop H. O. Wilson ensures that the life-changing message of Jesus Christ is accessible to people everywhere.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'body.p2', 'Sermons, teachings, and ministry events are available through our online video library, making biblical content accessible at any time. This ministry offers relevant, engaging, and Spirit-filled teaching designed to reach both young and old, meeting people where they are with the timeless truth of God’s Word. In a world that is constantly connected, the Worldwide Ministry serves as a digital mission field, equipping and inspiring believers globally.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'body.p3', 'This ministry also organizes live-streamed global prayer gatherings, allowing individuals from around the world to unite in worship and intercession. Online Bible study groups and discipleship courses create space for deeper learning, accountability, and community for those unable to attend in person.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'body.p4', 'The Worldwide Ministry exists not just to share content but to build relationships, foster discipleship, and create a global community of faith. By embracing technology, YDM fulfills the Great Commission in a way that is relevant to the digital age. Whether you are joining from across town or across the world, the Worldwide Ministry invites you to connect, grow, and encounter Christ online.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'hero.title', 'Worldwide Ministry (Online)', 'text'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'meta.title', 'Worldwide Ministry (Online)', 'text'),
  ('ministry.wordwide', 'sections.h3_1', 'WOrldwide Ministry - (Online)', 'text'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p1', 'In-Person: The Worship Ministry at Yeshua Deliverance Ministries is the heartbeat of our fellowship, where the presence of God is honored and His Word is proclaimed with clarity and passion. Led by Bishop H. O. Wilson, this ministry brings together preaching, teaching, and Spirit-led worship to inspire believers and invite seekers into a life-changing encounter with Christ. Monthly preaching and teaching services provide biblical instruction that is both relevant and practical, equipping individuals to apply God’s truth in daily living. Baptism services, a sacred celebration of new life in Christ, mark milestones of faith and strengthen our community. Beyond the pulpit, our worldwide video library allows members and friends to access sermons, teaching, and ministry events at their convenience, ensuring that the Word continues to build and nurture faith even outside church gatherings.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p2', 'In addition to regular gatherings, the Worship Ministry in-future seek to organize special worship nights and revival services that encourage spiritual renewal and deeper connection with God. These events provide opportunities for extended times of praise, intercession, and teaching that refresh the spirit and energize the soul. The ministry also invests in training worship leaders (and previously, musicians), ensuring that every aspect of worship is marked by excellence and a true heart of devotion.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p3', 'At its core, this ministry is not about performance but about ushering people into the presence of God, where healing, transformation, and deliverance take place. Whether you attend in person, watch online, or participate in a baptism celebration, the Worship Ministry is committed to helping you encounter the living Christ in a way that strengthens your walk and inspires your worship.', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p4', 'Worship Service – Every 4th Sunday of the month – 1:00 PMBible Study – Thursdays – 7:30pm', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p5', 'Mississauga Church of God(Inside the Savation Army Erin Mills Church)', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'body.p6', '2460 The Collegeway, Mississauga, ON L5L 1V3', 'richtext'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'hero.title', 'Worship Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'meta.description', '', 'text'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'meta.title', 'Worship Ministry', 'text'),
  ('ministry.worship', 'sections.h3_1', 'YDM Worship Ministry!', 'text'),
  ('our_campaigns', 'hero.subtitle', 'Your generosity moves the mission forward.', 'text'),
  ('our_campaigns', 'hero.title', 'Give', 'text'),
  ('our_campaigns', 'intro.body', 'At Yeshua Deliverance Ministries, our mission is to reach souls, build families, and impact communities with the love and power of Jesus Christ. Every donation you make is more than just a contribution — it is a seed of faith that fuels the growth and expansion of our ministries.', 'richtext'),
  ('our_campaigns', 'list.empty_state', 'No active campaigns at the moment.', 'text'),
